          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"chesspairdataset\"><code>ChessPairDataset</code></h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Reads the precomputed CSV. On <code>__getitem__</code> it picks <strong>one</strong> corruption\ncolumn according to <code>corruption_mix</code> (a 3-tuple summing to 1.0 over\n<code>corrupt_shuffle</code>, <code>corrupt_legal_move</code>, <code>corrupt_piece_swap</code> in that\norder) and returns three tensors: problem, clean trace, corrupted trace.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">FENs are stored as Python strings until <code>__getitem__</code> converts the\nchosen three to tensors \u2014 this keeps memory low (~70 MB for FENs vs\n~3+ GB if we precomputed every tensor).</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
